<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5122.1.1>
    dc:creator "Cancello, Eliana M.", "Chiquetto-Machado, Pedro I.", "Morales, Adriana C." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic revision of Paraphasma Redtenbacher, 1906 (Phasmatodea, Pseudophasmatidae) based on phallic and external morphology" ;
    bibo:endPage "80" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2022-03-30" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5122" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399542>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399588>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399590>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399592>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399594>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399596>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399598> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399542>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distribution map of Paraphasma. Circles indicate records based on material examined; triangles indicate records from the literature (Stoll 1787; Serville 1839; Chopard 1911; Conle et al. 2011; Jourdan et al. 2014); stars indicate records of undetermined Paraphasma species based on Rehn (1906) and Piza (1939) (although these authors identified the specimens, the identifications are doubtful or insufficient)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399542/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399588>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Paraphasma marginale Redtenbacher, 1906, male, paralectotype (NHMW). A–C. Habitus, dorsal (A), lateral (B) and ventral (C) views. D. Anterior region of the body, dorsolateral view. E. Labels. Scale bars = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399588/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399590>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Paraphasma marginale Redtenbacher, 1906, male terminalia. A–D. Terminalia in dorsal (A), lateral (B), ventral (C) and oblique caudal (D) views. E. Drawing of the vomer. Abbreviations: Ce, cerci; S8, sternite VIII; SPa, anterior region of the subgenital plate; SPp, posterior region of the subgenital plate; T8, T9, T10, tergites VIII, IX and X; TP, thorn pad. Arrows = expansion of the posterolateral margin of the subgenital plate. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399590/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399592>
    dc:description "FIGURE 22. Paraphasma marginale Redtenbacher, 1906, illustrations of the phallic organ. A. Dorsal view. B. Detail of the sclerite of the ventral lobe in dorsal view. C. Caudal view. D. Left view. E. Right view. Abbreviations: ap, apical protuberance of the sclerite of the ventral lobe; b, base; dl, dorsal lobe; dp, distal process of the dorsal sclerite; lp, left basal protuberance of the sclerite of the ventral lobe; rbp, right basal pouch; rp, right basal protuberance of the sclerite of the ventral lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Colors: light gray, membranous regions; red, dorsal sclerite; green, sclerite of the ventral lobe; blue, base apodemes. * = left ramification of the dorsal lobe. In D and E the final portion of the ejaculatory duct is represented by transparency with dotted lines. Images A, B, D and E adapted from Chiquetto-Machado & Cancello (2021: fig. 5)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399592/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399594>
    dc:description "FIGURE 23. Paraphasma marginale Redtenbacher, 1906, female, paralectotype (NHMW). A–C. Habitus, dorsal (A), lateral (B) and ventral (C) views. D. Anterior region of the body, dorsolateral view. E–G. Terminalia, dorsal (E), ventral (F) and lateral (G) views. H. Labels.Abbreviations: Ce, cerci; PO, praeopercular organ; SP, subgenital plate; T8, T9, T10, tergites VIII, IX and X. Arrow = anterodorsal carina of profemur. Scale bars = 10 mm, unless otherwise indicated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399594/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399596>
    dc:description "FIGURE 24. Paraphasma marginale Redtenbacher, 1906, egg. Dorsal (A), lateral (B) and anterodorsal (C) views, and drawing of the internal micropylar plate (D). Abbreviations: Ca, capsule; Op, operculum; MP, micropylar plate. White arrow = median line; black arrow = internal median line." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399596/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6399598>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. Paraphasma marginale Redtenbacher, 1906, live specimens. A. Adult male from Alto Paraíso de Goiás (Goiás, Brazil), dorsolateral habitus. B–D.Adult female from Delfinópolis (Minas Gerais, Brazil), lateral habitus (B) and anterior region of the body in dorsal (C) and dorsolateral (D) views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6399598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

